title: Horse-drawn wagon in front of the Art Institute of Chicago Holiday Cards
description:
This lovely vintage photograph features a man driving a horse-drawn wagon on a sidewalk during a snowstorm, next to one of the famous Edward Kemeys Lions at The Art Institute of Chicago in 1925.  The cards are made from a sustainable FSC certified mix paper and vegetable-based inks.

  • Card dimensions: 5 x 7 in.
  • Box dimensions: 5.625 x 7.625 x 1.375 in.
  • 20 cards and envelopes.
  • Interior message:  Season’s Greetings
